examples: Under some circumstances police are allowed to invade a person's privacy.

definitions.definition: To enter by force , usually in order to conquer .
examples: Argentinian troops invaded the Falkland Islands in 1982.
The picnic was invaded by ants.

definitions.definition: To attack; to infringe ; to encroach on; to violate .
examples: The king invaded the rights of the people.

definitions.definition: To make an unwelcome or uninvited visit or appearance, usually with an intent to cause trouble or some other unpleasant situation.

secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To enter by force , usually in order to conquer .
